quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  17,85,"They ask you ˹O Prophet˺ about the spirit. Say, “Its nature is known only to my Lord, and you ˹O humanity˺ have been given but little knowledge.”"
  17,86,"If We willed, We could have certainly taken away what We have revealed to you ˹O Prophet˺—then you would find none to guarantee its return from Us—"
  17,87,"had it not been for the mercy of your Lord. Indeed, His favour upon you is immense"
  17,88,"Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “If ˹all˺ humans and jinn were to come together to produce the equivalent of this Quran, they could not produce its equal, no matter how they supported each other.”"
  17,89,"And We have truly set forth every ˹kind of˺ lesson for humanity in this Quran, yet most people persist in disbelief"
  17,90,"They challenge ˹the Prophet˺, “We will never believe in you until you cause a spring to gush forth from the earth for us"
  17,91,"or until you have a garden of palm trees and vineyards, and cause rivers to flow abundantly in it"
  17,92,"or cause the sky to fall upon us in pieces, as you have claimed, or bring Allah and the angels before us, face to face"
  17,93,"or until you have a house of gold, or you ascend into heaven—and even then we will not believe in your ascension until you bring down to us a book that we can read.” Say, “Glory be to my Lord! Am I not only a human messenger?”"